HEADWORD: Paulist
<hw>Paul"ist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld>
<def>A member of <org>The Institute of the Missionary Priests of St.
Paul the Apostle</org>, founded in 1858 by the <person>Rev. I. T.
Hecker</person> of <city>New York</city>. The majority of the members
were formerly Protestants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

